entities.description: An experience or indicator of depression, such as feeling sad, empty, or discouraged most of the day.
Loss of interest or pleasure in most things.
Problems related to sleep, such as difficulties falling or staying asleep.
Experience of restlessness or lethargy as noticed by others.
Feeling tired or having low energy nearly every day.

Indicates that the survey respondent has experienced problems related to sleep.
Indicates that others have noticed the survey respondent being restless or lethargic.
Indicates that the survey respondent feels tired or has low energy nearly every day.
